==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Latinism
<hw>Lat"in*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>latinisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Latin idiom; a mode of speech
peculiar to Latin; also, a mode of speech in another language, as
English, formed on a Latin model.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term is also sometimes used by Biblical scholars to
designate a Latin word in Greek letters, or the Latin sense of a Greek
word in the Greek Testament.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Latinist</ent>⟦br⟧
